=Description=

"Networking City is written by SeunghoYoo, a doctoral researcher at Centre for Advanced Spatial Analysis (CASA), The Bartlett, University College London (UCL) . He is an urban researcher and architect, working in the field of architecture, social science and urban design. As an urban researcher, his main focus is on the relationship between internet technology and public space, civil participation and governance. His work in architecture is related to cultural programme, industrial building and renovation. He finished his bachelor's and master's degree in architectural design at Hanyang University, South Korea, and graduated MSc. Contemporary Urbanism at London School of Economics."
